-- Cognizant quarterly net income rises 20 percent
-- 
-- Mon Feb 5, 2007 6:42am EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/02/05/us-cognizant-results-idUSWEN352020070205

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - Cognizant Technology Solutions Corp. ( CTSH.O ), which provides software services, on Monday reported a 21 percent increase in quarterly profit as it won more deals in Europe and in the health care industry. 


 Net income rose to $69.5 million, or 46 cents per share, from $57.7 million, or 39 cents per share, a year earlier. Revenue advanced to $424.4 million from $256.9 million. Excluding costs from stock-based compensation, quarterly diluted earnings per share were 50 cents. The company in November had forecast fourth-quarter net income per share of 42 cents, or profit of 47 cents excluding stock-based compensation costs, and revenue of at least $405 million.